# Fix: Query Timeout on "summarize the plot of 2001 Space Odyssey"

## Root Cause Analysis

The user sees **"The request timed out"** — this comes from [api_client.py:38-41](file:///D:/Evolve_Robot_Lab/Project/FilmDB_Demo/ui/api_client.py#L38-L41) when the backend `/chat` response takes longer than **120 seconds**.

Three bottlenecks stack on top of each other:

| # | Bottleneck | Where | Worst case |
|---|-----------|-------|------------|
| 1 | **Parquet cold-start** | [FilmDBQueryEngine.__init__](file:///D:/Evolve_Robot_Lab/Project/FilmDB_Demo/rag/filmdb_query_engine.py#L37-L76) loads **~416 MB** of parquet + builds title/person indices on the **first request** | 30-60s |
| 2 | **Groq LLM — no timeout** | [GroqClient._chat](file:///D:/Evolve_Robot_Lab/Project/FilmDB_Demo/backend/app/llm/groq_client.py#L31-L43) calls Groq API with **no timeout** parameter. Up to 3 calls per request (intent + response + grounding retry) | 30s+ each |
| 3 | **Wikipedia optional tool** | [routing_matrix.py](file:///D:/Evolve_Robot_Lab/Project/FilmDB_Demo/backend/app/routing_matrix.py#L20) routes `PLOT_EXPLANATION` with `optional: ["kb_entity", "wikipedia"]` — Wikipedia API can add **15s** if it times out | 15s |

**Combined worst case**: 60s (parquet) + 90s (3× Groq calls) + 15s (Wikipedia) = **165s** > 120s UI timeout.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The parquet cold-start only affects the **very first request** after the backend starts. Subsequent requests reuse the singleton. However, the Groq timeout issue affects **every** request.

---

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Eager-load parquet at startup

#### [MODIFY] [main.py](file:///D:/Evolve_Robot_Lab/Project/FilmDB_Demo/backend/app/main.py)

Pre-load the [FilmDBQueryEngine](file:///d:/Evolve_Robot_Lab/Project/FilmDB_Demo/rag/filmdb_query_engine.py#32-436) singleton during FastAPI [startup](file:///d:/Evolve_Robot_Lab/Project/FilmDB_Demo/backend/app/main.py#17-20) instead of lazily on first request:

```python
@app.on_event("startup")
def startup() -> None:
    init_db()
    # Eager-load parquet data so first request isn't slow
    from rag.filmdb_query_engine import FilmDBQueryEngine
    FilmDBQueryEngine.get_instance()
```

---

### 2. Add timeout to Groq LLM calls

#### [MODIFY] [groq_client.py](file:///D:/Evolve_Robot_Lab/Project/FilmDB_Demo/backend/app/llm/groq_client.py)

Add a `timeout` parameter to the Groq API call. The Groq Python SDK supports this:

```python
def _chat(self, messages: list[dict[str, str]], temperature: float) -> str:
    if not self.client:
        return ""
    try:
        response = self.client.chat.completions.create(
            model=self.model,
            messages=cast(Any, messages),
            temperature=temperature,
            timeout=30.0,  # 30 second timeout per LLM call
        )
        return response.choices[0].message.content or ""
    except Exception:
        logging.exception("Groq request failed")
        return ""
```

---

### 3. Add overall request timeout in conversation engine

#### [MODIFY] [conversation_engine.py](file:///D:/Evolve_Robot_Lab/Project/FilmDB_Demo/backend/app/conversation_engine.py)

Wrap the [_execute_tools](file:///d:/Evolve_Robot_Lab/Project/FilmDB_Demo/backend/app/conversation_engine.py#450-582) `asyncio.gather` with `asyncio.wait_for` to cap total tool execution time. Add a per-tool timeout:

```python
# In _execute_tools, wrap gather with overall timeout
try:
    results = await asyncio.wait_for(
        asyncio.gather(*tasks, return_exceptions=True),
        timeout=45.0  # max 45s for all tools combined
    )
except asyncio.TimeoutError:
    self.logger.warning("Tool execution timed out after 45s")
    results = [TimeoutError("Tool execution timed out") for _ in tasks]
```

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The changes above address 3 independent bottlenecks. The most impactful are **#1** (parquet cold-start) and **#2** (Groq timeout). Would you like me to proceed with all 3, or just the first two?

> [!NOTE]
> After these fixes, the expected request timeline becomes:
> - Intent classification: ~2-3s (Groq, with 30s cap)
> - Tool execution: ~0.5-2s (KB parquet lookups are instant; Wikipedia is optional)
> - Response generation: ~3-5s (Groq, with 30s cap)
> - **Total: ~6-10s** (well within the 120s UI timeout)

